column2: SELECT CASE WHEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'end trip' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'end trip' THEN timestamp END) WHEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'declaration rejected by employee' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'declaration rejected by employee' THEN timestamp END) WHEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'payment handled' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MAX(CASE WHEN activity = 'payment handled' THEN timestamp END) END AS last_event_timestamp, MIN(timestamp) AS first_event_timestamp, last_event_timestamp - first_event_timestamp AS time_elapsed FROM event_log WHERE idcase = '12345' GROUP BY idcase;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT CASE WHEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'end trip' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'end trip' THEN timestamp END) WHEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'declaration rejected by employee' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'declaration rejected by employee' THEN timestamp END) WHEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'payment handled' THEN timestamp END) IS NOT NULL THEN MIN(CASE WHEN activity = 'payment handled' THEN timestamp END) END - MIN(timestamp) FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT "idcase", ( JULIANDAY("timestamp") - MIN(JULIANDAY("timestamp")) OVER (PARTITION BY "idcase") ) * 24 * 60 * 60 AS "time_elapsed" FROM "event_log" WHERE "activity" IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ORDER BY "idcase", "timestamp";
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT MIN(el1."timestamp") AS "first_action_timestamp", MAX(el2."timestamp") AS "last_action_timestamp", el1."activity" AS "first_action", el2."activity" AS "last_action", el1."resource" AS "first_action_resource", el2."resource" AS "last_action_resource" FROM "event_log" AS el1 JOIN "event_log" AS el2 ON el1."idcase" = el2."idcase" WHERE el1."activity" IN ( 'Declaration created', 'Declaration submitted', 'Declaration rejected by employee', 'Payment made' ) AND el2."activity" IN ( 'Trip finalized', 'Declaration rejected by employee', 'Payment made' ) GROUP BY el1."idcase" ORDER BY "first_action_timestamp";
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT MIN(el1."timestamp") AS "first_intervention_timestamp", MAX(el2."timestamp") AS "last_intervention_timestamp", el1."activity" AS "first_intervention_activity", el2."activity" AS "last_intervention_activity" FROM "event_log" AS el1 JOIN "event_log" AS el2 ON el1."idcase" = el2."idcase" WHERE el1."activity" IN ('Intervention', 'Intervention - End of trip', 'Intervention - Declaration rejected by employee', 'Intervention - Payment already made') AND el2."activity" IN ('Intervention', 'Intervention - End of trip', 'Intervention - Declaration rejected by employee', 'Intervention - Payment already made') GROUP BY el1."idcase" ORDER BY "first_intervention_timestamp";
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT el1."idcase", el1."activity" AS "first_activity", el1."timestamp" AS "first_timestamp", el2."activity" AS "last_activity", el2."timestamp" AS "last_timestamp", (el2."timestamp" - el1."timestamp") AS "time_between_activities" FROM "event_log" AS el1 JOIN "event_log" AS el2 ON el1."idcase" = el2."idcase" WHERE el1."activity" = 'start trip' AND el2."activity" IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ORDER BY el1."idcase", el2."timestamp";
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column2: SELECT el1."idcase", el1."activity" AS "start_activity", el1."timestamp" AS "start_timestamp", el2."activity" AS "end_activity", el2."timestamp" AS "end_timestamp", (el2."timestamp" - el1."timestamp") AS "duration" FROM "event_log" AS el1 JOIN "event_log" AS el2 ON el1."idcase" = el2."idcase" WHERE el1."activity" IN ('start trip', 'declaration submitted') AND el2."activity" IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ORDER BY el1."timestamp";
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column2: SELECT CASE WHEN MIN(el1.timestamp) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE ( MAX(el2.timestamp) - MIN(el1.timestamp) ) END AS time_taken, el1.idcase, el2.activity FROM event_log AS el1 JOIN event_log AS el2 ON el1.idcase = el2.idcase WHERE el1.activity IN ('start trip', 'declaration submitted by employee') AND el2.activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') GROUP BY el1.idcase, el2.activity;

column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase
